The paper proposes a novel reinforcement learning-based method for short-term load forecasting. The method involves building a forecasting model pool and selecting the best model at each time step using a Q-learning agent. This approach involves machine learning, artificial intelligence, and control systems, which are all subcategories of computer science. Therefore, the most likely subcategories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves numerical simulations, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
